eh .env cannot be named nga

That happens because Mac Finder sometimes blocks filenames starting with ., but we can bypass it easily. Don’t worry — this is very normal.

Since your server is already running, first stop it.

In Terminal press:

Control + C
You should see your normal cursor again.

Create .env the reliable way (Terminal)
Make sure you are inside your project folder:

cd ~/Desktop/nursing-ncp-system
Now run this command:

nano .env
This creates the file even if Finder refuses it.

You will see a simple text editor in Terminal.

Paste this:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
APP_PASSWORD=VeryStrongPassword123
PORT=3000
FRONTEND_ORIGIN=null
Replace the API key with yours.

Save the file
Press:

Control + O
then press Enter

Then exit:

Control + X
Check if the file exists
Run:

ls -la
You should now see:

.env
server.mjs
package.json
node_modules
The -a shows hidden files like .env.

Restart the server
Run again:

node server.mjs
Test again
Open Safari and go to:

http://localhost:3000/health
If everything worked, you should now see:

{"ok":true,"aiReady":true}
If you want, I can also show you the final step that connects your Nursing Care Plan website to this secure backend so the AI diagnosis generator actually works.


huh what api key will i replace with mine?

Good question — you need an OpenAI API key.

That is the key that allows your backend (server.js / server.mjs) to talk to the AI to generate nursing diagnoses and interventions.

You get it from OpenAI.

How to get your API key
1️⃣ Go to the OpenAI platform
Open Safari and go to:

https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
Sign in with your account.

2️⃣ Create a key
Click:

Create new secret key
You will see something like:

sk-proj-abc123xyz456...
Copy it.

⚠️ You will only see it once.

3️⃣ Put it in your .env file
Open the .env file you created and replace this:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
with your real key, for example:

OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-abc123xyz456
Do not add quotes.

4️⃣ Save the file
Then restart the server.

Stop the server:

Ctrl + C
Run it again:

node server.mjs
5️⃣ Test again
Open:

http://localhost:3000/health
If successful you will see:

{"ok":true,"aiReady":true}
That means AI is now connected to your NCP generator.

Important security rule
Never put the API key in your HTML file.

It must stay only in:

.env
because:

HTML can be viewed by anyone

.env stays on your computer/server

